## Issues


### incident 0
incident to fix: "Leverage a Maven profile to run the Quarkus native build adding the following section to the `pom.xml` file: 

 ```xml
 <profiles>
 <profile>
 <id>native</id>
 <activation>
 <property>
 <name>native</name>
 </property>
 </activation>
 <properties>
 <skipITs>false</skipITs>
 <quarkus.package.type>native</quarkus.package.type>
 </properties>
 </profile>
 </profiles>
 ```"

## Reasoning
To address the issue, we need to add a Maven profile to the `pom.xml` file to run the Quarkus native build. This profile will be activated when the `native` property is set. The profile will set the `skipITs` property to `false` and the `quarkus.package.type` property to `native`. This will allow us to build a native executable for our Quarkus application.
